der-17 football team|England U17]]{{citation needed|date=July 2019}}\n| nationalcaps2 = 9\n| nationalgoals2 = 2\n| nationalyears3 = 2016\n| nationalteam3 = [[England national under-18 football team|England U18]]{{citation needed|date=July 2019}}\n| nationalcaps3 = 5\n| nationalgoals3 = 3\n| nationalyears4 = 2017\u20132018\n| nationalteam4 = [[England national under-19 football team|England U19]]<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.englandfootballonline.com/MatchRsl/MatchRslTmU19pg2.html |title=England's matches: The under 19's: 2010\u201320 |website=England Football Online |date=9 April 2019 |accessdate=20 July 2019}}</ref>\n| nationalcaps4 = 16\n| nationalgoals4 = 7\n| nationalyears5 = 2018\u2013\n| nationalteam5 = [[England national under-21 football team|England U21]]<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.englandfootballonline.com/MatchRsl/MatchRslTmU21pg4.html |title=England's matches: The under 21's: 2010\u201320 |website=England Football Online |date=9 September 2019 |accessdate=6 October 2019}}</ref>\n| nationalcaps5 = 4\n| nationalgoals5 = 1\n| nationalyears6 = 2019\u2013\n| nationalteam6 = [[England national football team|England]]\n| nationalcaps6 = 6\n| nationalgoals6 = 1\n| club-update = 16:03, 8 March 2020 (UTC)\n| nationalteam-update = 20:07, 17 November 2019 (UTC)\n}}\n'''Mason Tony Mount''' (born 10 January 1999) is an English professional [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[midfielder]] for {{English football updater|Chelsea}} club [[Chelsea F.C.|Chelsea]] and the [[England national football team|England national team]]. \n\nHe joined Chelsea at the age of six, and began his senior career on loan to [[SBV Vitesse|Vitesse]] in the Dutch [[Eredivisie]] and [[Derby County]] in the [[EFL Championship|Championship]] before making his Chelsea debut in 2019.the best midfielder ever\n\n==Club career==\n===Chelsea===\n====Youth levels====\n[[File:Mount in 2016.png|thumb|upright|Mount playing for [[Chelsea F.C. Under-23s and Academy|Chelsea U18]] in 2016]]\n\nMount was born in [[Portsmouth]], Hampshire.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.portsmouth.co.uk/sport/football/portsmouth-born-talent-signs-for-chelsea-1-7161622 |title=Portsmouth-born talent signs for Chelsea |first=Jeff |last=Marshman |newspaper=The News |location=Portsmouth |date=15 January 2016 |accessdate=10 October 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180428190724/https://www.portsmouth.co.uk/sport/football/portsmouth-born-talent-signs-for-chelsea-1-7161622 |archive-date=28 April 2018 |url-status=dead }}</ref> His father Tony was a player and manager at [[Non-league football|non-league level]] with local clubs such as [[Havant Town F.C.|Havant Town]].<ref name=wait>[https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/52054333 Mason Mount: How midfielder ended Chelsea's long wait for homegrown star], BBC Sport, 8 April 2020</ref> He was playing under-6 football in local leagues as a four-year-old and spent one day a week training in the academies of [[Portsmouth F.C.|Portsmouth]], [[Southampton F.C.|Southampton]] and [[Chelsea F.C.|Chelsea]].<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.vi.nl/pro/overig/mason-mount-vitesse-pareltje-dat-uitzondering-op-chelsea-regel-moet-worden |title=Mason Mount, Vitesse-pareltje dat uitzondering op Chelsea-regel moet worden |trans-title=Mason Mount, Vitesse gem that should be the exception to Chelsea rule |first=Stef |last=De Bont |website=Voetbal International |date=14 December 2017 |accessdate=10 October 2018 |language=Dutch}}</ref> Mount joined Chelsea at the age of six, in 2005.<ref name=wait/><ref>{{cite news |last1=Fordham |first1=Josh |title=Chelsea starlet Mason Mount signs new five-year contract after impressing on loan with Frank Lampard at Derby County |url=https://talksport.com/football/573242/mason-mount-contract-chelsea-derby/ |accessdate=22 August 2019 |publisher=Talksport |date=15 July 2019|quote=Mount added: \"I joined this club at six-years-old and it was always my goal to play for the first-team one day.}}</ref> He made his [[Chelsea F.C. Under-23s and Academy|under-18]] debut as an under-15 during the [[2013\u201314 Chelsea F.C. season|2013\u201314 season]] and added several more appearances in the [[2014\u201315 Chelsea F.C. season|following season]].{{citation needed|date=October 2018}} Mount went on to play for both under-18 and under-21 teams during the [[2016\u201317 Chelsea F.C. season|2016\u201317 season]], in which he scored 10 goals in 30 appearances.{{citation needed|date=October 2018}} He signed a new four-year contract with Chelsea in July 2017.<ref name=Contract>{{cite web |url=http://www.chelseafc.com/news/latest-news/2017/07/mount-signs-new-deal-and-heads-to-vitesse.html |title=Mount signs new deal and heads to Vitesse |publisher=Chelsea F.C. |date=24 July 2017 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20171007232919/http://www.chelseafc.com/news/latest-news/2017/07/mount-signs-new-deal-and-heads-to-vitesse.html |archivedate=7 October 2017}}</ref>\n\n====Loans to Vitesse and Derby County====\nMount joined Dutch [[Eredivisie]] club [[SBV Vitesse|Vitesse]] on 24 July 2017 on a season-long [[Loan (sports)|loan]].<ref name=Contract/> He made his first-team debut on 26 August, as a 77th-minute [[Substitute (association football)|substitute]] during Vitesse's 2\u20131 home defeat against [[AZ Alkmaar|AZ]].<ref name=Soccerway/><ref>{{cite web |url=https://uk.soccerway.com/matches/2017/08/26/netherlands/eredivisie/sbv-vitesse/stichting-az/2462357/ |title=Vitesse vs. AZ 1\u20132 |website=Soccerway |publisher=Perform Group |accessdate=10 October 2018}}</ref> The following month, he was given his first start in Vitesse's [[KNVB Cup]] first-round defeat away to fifth-tier team [[AVV Swift|Swift]], playing the full 90 minutes of the 0\u20130 draw, which Swift won in a [[Penalty shoot-out (association football)|penalty shoot-out]].<ref name=Soccerway/><ref>{{cite web |url=https://uk.soccerway.com/matches/2017/09/20/netherlands/knvb-beker/swift/sbv-vitesse/2580810/ |title=Swift vs. Vitesse 0\u20130 |website=Soccerway |publisher=Perform Group |accessdate=10 October 2018}}</ref> He scored his first goal for Vitesse on 1 October in the 76th minute of a 1\u20131 home draw with [[FC Utrecht|Utrecht]].<ref name=Soccerway/><ref>{{cite web |url=https://uk.soccerway.com/matches/2017/10/01/netherlands/eredivisie/sbv-vitesse/stichting-fc-utrecht/2462399/ |title=Vitesse vs. Utrecht 1\u20131 |website=Soccerway |publisher=Perform Group |accessdate=10 October 2018}}</ref> Mount went onto appear in the Eredivisie Team of the Week on several occasions and win the Vitesse Player of the Year award.<ref name=VitessePOTY>{{cite web |url=https://weaintgotnohistory.sbnation.com/2018/4/29/17299438/mason-mount-becomes-third-chelsea-loanee-to-win-vitesse-player-of-the-year-award |title=Mason Mount becomes third Chelsea loanee to win Vitesse Player of the Year award |first=Ram |last=Srinivas |website=We Ain't Got No History |publisher=Vox Media |date=29 April 2018 |accessdate=10 October 2018}}</ref>\n\nDuring Vitesse's Eredivisie European play-off semi-final first leg against [[ADO Den Haag]] on 9 May 2018, Mount scored his first hat-trick, as Vitesse won 5\u20132 away.<ref name=Soccerway/> In the second leg, Mount scored in a 2\u20131 win as Vitesse won 7\u20133 on aggregate.<ref name=Soccerway/> In the first leg of the final against Utrecht, Mount opened the scoring but was booked and therefore suspended for the second leg.<ref name=Soccerway/> Mount made 39 appearances in all competitions for Vitesse, scoring 14 times, before returning to Chelsea.\n\nMount joined [[EFL Championship|Championship]] club [[Derby County F.C.|Derby County]] on 17 July 2018 on a season-long loan.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/44860172 |title=Derby County sign youngsters Mason Mount and Harry Wilson on loan |website=BBC Sport |date=17 July 2018 |accessdate=17 July 2018}}</ref> He scored a 60th-minute equaliser on his debut for Derby on 3 August 2018, during a 2\u20131 away victory over [[Reading F.C.|Reading]].<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/44976502 |title=Reading 1\u20132 Derby County |first=Adam |last=Williams |website=BBC Sport |date=3 August 2018 |accessdate=10 October 2018}}</ref>\n\nMount was sidelined for two months after suffering a [[hamstring injury]] in a [[FA Cup]] game against [[Accrington Stanley F.C.|Accrington Stanley]].<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.portsmouth.co.uk/news/fa-cup-mason-mount-injured-as-derby-edge-accrington-wolves-deny-shrewsbury-doncaster-join-portsmouth-and-qpr-in-hat-1-8785996 |title=FA Cup: Mason Mount injured as Derby edge Accrington\u2026 Wolves deny Shrewsbury\u2026  Doncaster join Portsmouth and QPR in hat |newspaper=The News |date=26 January 2019 |accessdate=2 April 2019}}</ref> He returned in a 6\u20131 win over [[Rotherham United F.C.|Rotherham United]], winning a penalty for teammate [[Martyn Waghorn]] and later scoring.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/47676104 |title=Derby County 6\u20131 Rotherham United |website=BBC Sport |date=30 March 2019 |accessdate=2 April 2019}}</ref> Two weeks later, he scored his first senior [[hat-trick]] in a 4\u20130 [[EFL Championship|Championship]] league game against [[Bolton Wanderers F.C.|Bolton Wanderers]],<ref>{{cite web |url=https://tribuna.com/en/chelsea/news/3351509/ |title=Mount scores first senior hat-trick sending Derby closer to premier league promotion |publisher=Fedor Gavrilov |date=13 April 2019 |accessdate=16 April 2019}}</ref> keeping Derby in contention for the promotion [[EFL Championship play-offs|playoff]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.derbytelegraph.co.uk/sport/football/football-news/gallery/best-pictures-mason-mount-hat-2756168 |title=The best pictures as Mason Mount hat-trick keeps Derby County play-off hopes alive |publisher=Jonny Bonell |date=13 April 2019 |accessdate=16 April 2019}}</ref>\n\n====First-team breakthrough====\nOn 15 July 2019, Mount signed a new five-year deal with Chelsea.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.chelseafc.com/en/news/2019/07/15/mason-mount-commits-to-chelsea-with-new-contract-signed |title=MASON MOUNT COMMITS TO CHELSEA WITH NEW CONTRACT SIGNED |publisher=Chelsea F.C. |date=15 July 2019 |accessdate=16 July 2019}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/48993844 |title=Mason Mount: Chelsea midfielder signs five-year contract |date=15 July 2019 |website=BBC Sport}}</ref> He made his competitive debut for Chelsea on 11 August 2019 in a 0\u20134 away defeat to [[Manchester United F.C.|Manchester United]] in the [[Premier League]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.chelseafc.com/en/news/2019/08/11/report--manchester-united-v-chelsea |title=REPORT: MAN UNITED 4 CHELSEA 0 |publisher=Chelsea F.C. |date=11 August 2019 |accessdate=11 August 2019}}</ref> He scored his first Chelsea goal a week later against [[Leicester City F.C.|Leicester City]] during [[Frank Lampard]]'s home debut as manager at [[Stamford Bridge (stadium)|Stamford Bridge]], a 1\u20131 draw,<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.goal.com/en/match/chelsea-v-leicester-city/6ksyqoht9ras6zwyvks09fofe|title=Chelsea 1-1 Leicester City: Mount hits the heights before Foxes bite back|date=18 August 2019|website=Goal}}</ref> and added another in the next game away to [[Norwich City F.C.|Norwich City]].<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.chelseafc.com/en/news/2019/08/24/match-report--norwich-city-vs-chelsea|title=MATCH REPORT: NORWICH CITY 2 CHELSEA 3 |date=24 August 2019|website=Goal}}</ref> On 17 September, he suffered an ankle injury against [[Valencia CF|Valencia]] in the [[2019\u201320 UEFA Champions League|Champions League]] opener.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/49736574|title=Mason Mount injury: Chelsea to assess ankle over next 48 hours|date=17 September 2019|publisher=BBC Sport}}</ref>\n\nIn March 2020, Mount was spoken to by Chelsea for ignoring [[Self-isolating|self-isolation]] rules during the [[2020 coronavirus pandemic in the United Kingdom|coronavirus pandemic]]. While the entire squad was made to self-isolate due to the infection of [[Callum Hudson-Odoi]], Mount had gone to play football with friends including West Ham's [[Declan Rice]].<ref>{{cite news |last1=Hytner |first1=David |title=Chelsea act after Mason Mount ignores coronavirus self-isolation advice |url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/2020/mar/16/mason-mount-warned-by-chelsea-after-breaking-coronavirus-self-isolation |accessdate=5 April 2020 |work=The Guardian |date=16 March 2020}}</ref>\n\n==International career==\n===Youth===\nMount has represented England at [[England national under-16 football team|under-16]], [[England national under-17 football team|under-17]], [[England national under-18 football team|under-18]] and [[England national under-19 football team|under-19]] levels.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.thefa.com/england/all-teams/players?p=356955 |title=Mason Mount |publisher=The Football Association |accessdate=12 August 2017}}{{dead link|date=October 2018}}</ref> Mount represented the under-17s at the [[2016 UEFA European Under-17 Championship]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.thefa.com/news/2016/may/04/euro-finals-squad-announced-040516 |title=England under-17s squad named for Euro Championship |first=Nicholas |last=Veevers |publisher=The Football Association |date=4 May 2016 |accessdate=10 October 2018}}</ref>\n\nMount was included in the under-19 team for the [[2017 UEFA European Under-19 Championship]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.thefa.com/news/2017/jun/26/england-u19-squad-for-euros-260617 |title=Squad for U19 Euro |publisher=The Football Association |date=26 June 2017 |accessdate=10 October 2018}}</ref> He provided the assist for [[Lukas Nmecha]] to score the winning goal against [[Portugal national under-19 football team|Portugal]] in the final.<ref name=U19>{{cite web |url=http://www.thefa.com/news/2017/jul/15/report-2017-uefa-u19-championship-final-portugal-england-150717 |title=Portugal 1\u20132 England U19s |first=Andy |last=Walker |publisher=The Football Association |date=15 July 2017 |accessdate=10 October 2018}}</ref> He was subsequently named [[UEFA European Under-19 Championship#Golden Player Award|Golden Player]] of the tournament.<ref name=GoldenPlayer>{{cite web |url=https://www.uefa.com/under19/history/season=2017/goldenplayer/index.html |title=2017: Mason Mount |publisher=UEFA |date=25 July 2017 |accessdate=10 October 2018}}</ref>\n\nOn 27 May 2019, Mount was included in England's 23-man squad for the [[2019 UEFA European Under-21 Championship]].<ref>{{Cite news |title=ENGLAND U21S SQUAD NAMED BY AIDY BOOTHROYD FOR THIS SUMMER'S EURO FINALS IN ITALY |url=http://www.thefa.com/news/2019/may/26/england-u21s-squad-named-for-euros-270519 |publisher=The Football Association |date=27 May 2019 |accessdate=19 June 2019}}</ref>\n\n===Senior===\nFollowing his impressive season with Vitesse, Mount was invited by manager [[Gareth Southgate]] to train with the [[England national football team|senior team]] for a week ahead of the [[2018 FIFA World Cup]].<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.portsmouth.co.uk/sport/football/pompey/portsmouth-born-mount-to-train-with-southgate-s-england-squad-1-8503986 |title=Portsmouth-born Mount to train with Southgate's England squad |first=Will |last=Rooney |newspaper=The News |location=Portsmouth |date=18 May 2018 |accessdate=10 October 2018}}</ref> He was called up to the senior team for the [[UEFA Nations League]] matches against [[Croatia national football team|Croatia]] and [[Spain national football team|Spain]] in October 2018.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/45744731 |title=James Maddison, Jadon Sancho and Mason Mount named in England squad |website=BBC Sport |date=4 October 2018 |accessdate=10 October 2018}}</ref>\n\nMount made his debut for the England senior team on 7 September 2019 as a 67th-minute substitute in England's 4\u20130 home win over [[Bulgaria national football team|Bulgaria]] in [[UEFA Euro 2020 qualifying]].<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/49533275 |title=England 4\u20130 Bulgaria |first=Phil |last=McNulty |website=BBC Sport |date=7 September 2019 |accessdate=7 September 2019}}</ref> He scored his first goal for England on 17 November in a 4\u20130 away win against [[Kosovo national football team|Kosovo]] in UEFA Euro 2020 qualifying.<ref name=Kosovo>{{cite news |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/50160458 |title=Kosovo 0\u20134 England |first=Phil |last=McNulty |website=BBC Sport |date=17 November 2019 |accessdate=17 November 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Career statistics==\n===Club===\n{{updated|match played 8 March 2020}}\n\n{| class=wikitable style=text-align:center\n|+ Appearances and goals by club, season and competition\n|-\n!rowspan=2|Club\n!rowspan=2|Season\n!colspan=3|League\n!colspan=2|National Cup{{efn|Includes [[KNVB Cup]], [[FA Cup]]}}\n!colspan=2|League Cup{{efn|Includes [[EFL Cup]]}}\n!colspan=2|Europe\n!colspan=2|Other\n!colspan=2|Total\n|-\n!Division!!Apps!!Goals!!Apps!!Goals!!Apps!!Goals!!Apps!!Goals!!Apps!!Goals!!Apps!!Goals\n|-\n|[[Chelsea F.C. Under-23s and Academy|Chelsea U23]]\n|[[2016\u201317 EFL Trophy|2016\u201317]]<ref name=sb1617>{{soccerbase season|96788|2016|accessdate=10 October 2018}}</ref>\n|colspan=3|\u2014||colspan=2|\u2014||colspan=2|\u2014||colspan=2|\u2014||3{{efn|Appearances in [[EFL Trophy]]}}||0||3||0\n|-\n|[[SBV Vitesse|Vitesse]] (loan)\n|[[2017\u201318 SBV Vitesse season|2017\u201318]]<ref name=\"Soccerway\">{{cite web |url=https://uk.soccerway.com/players/mason-mount/376697/ |title=M. Mount: Summary |website=Soccerway |publisher=Perform Group |accessdate=10 October 2018}}</ref>\n|[[Eredivisie]]\n|29||9||1||0|| colspan=\"2\" |\u2014||6{{efn|Appearances in [[UEFA Europa League]]}}||0||3{{efn|Appearances in [[Eredivisie]] European play-offs}}||5||39||14\n|-\n|[[Derby County F.C.|Derby County]] (loan)\n|[[2018\u201319 Derby County F.C. season|2018\u201319]]<ref name=\"sb1819\">{{soccerbase season|96788|2018|accessdate=19 July 2019}}</ref>\n|[[EFL Championship|Championship]]\n|35||8||2||0||4||2|| colspan=\"2\" |\u2014||3{{efn|Appearances in [[EFL Championship play-offs]]}}||1||44||11\n|-\n|[[Chelsea F.C.|Chelsea]]\n|[[2019\u201320 Chelsea F.C. season|2019\u201320]]<ref name=sb1920>{{soccerbase season|96788|2019|accessdate=14 November 2019}}</ref>\n|[[Premier League]]\n|29||6||3||0||1||0||7{{efn|Appearances in [[UEFA Champions League]]}}||0||1{{efn|Appearance in [[UEFA Super Cup]]}}||0||41||6\n|-\n!colspan=3|Career total\n!93||23||6||0||5||2||13||0||10||6||127||31\n|}\n\n{{notelist}}\n\n===International===\n{{updated|match played 17 November 2019}}<ref name=NFT>{{NFT player |id=75408 |name=Mount, Mason |accessdate=17 November 2019}}<br />{{cite news |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/50160458 |title=Kosovo 0\u20134 England |first=Phil |last=McNulty |website=BBC Sport |date=17 November 2019 |accessdate=17 November 2019}}</ref>\n\n{| class=wikitable style=text-align:center\n|+ Appearances and goals by national team and year\n|-\n!National team!!Year!!Apps!!Goals\n|-\n|[[England national football team|England]]\n|2019||6||1\n|-\n!colspan=2|Total||6||1\n|}\n\n===International goals===\n:''As of match played 17 November 2019. England score listed first, score column indicates score after each Mount goal.''<ref name=NFT/>\n\t\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\"\n|+ International goals by date, venue, cap, opponent, score, result and competition\n|-\n!scope=col|No.\n!scope=col|Date\n!scope=col|Venue\n!scope=col|Cap\n!scope=col|Opponent\n!scope=col|Score\n!scope=col|Result\n!scope=col|Competition\n!scope=col class=unsortable|{{abbr|Ref.|Reference}}\n|-\n!scope=row style=text-align:center|1\n|17 November 2019||[[Fadil Vokrri Stadium]], Pristina, Kosovo||align=center|6||{{fb|Kosovo}}||align=center|4\u20130||align=center|4\u20130||[[UEFA Euro 2020 qualification]]||align=center|<ref name=\"Kosovo\"/>\n|}\n\n==Honours==\n'''Chelsea Youth'''\n*[[FA Youth Cup]]: [[2015\u201316 FA Youth Cup|2015\u201316]],<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.thefa.com/news/2016/apr/22/fa-youth-cup-final-first-leg-report |title=Honours even after first leg of 2015/16 FA Youth Cup Final |publisher=The Football Association |date=22 April 2016 |accessdate=10 October 2018}}<br />{{cite web |url=http://www.thefa.com/news/2016/apr/27/chelsea-3-1-manchester-city-fa-youth-cup-final-second-leg |title=Chelsea win the FA Youth Cup for third successive season |publisher=The Football Association |date=27 April 2016 |accessdate=10 October 2018}}</ref> [[2016\u201317 FA Youth Cup|2016\u201317]]<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.thefa.com/news/2017/apr/18/fa-youth-cup-final-first-leg-180417 |title=All square in FA Youth Cup Final between Man City and Chelsea |publisher=The Football Association |date=18 April 2017 |accessdate=10 October 2018}}<br />{{cite web |url=http://www.thefa.com/news/2017/apr/26/chelsea-manchester-city-fa-youth-cup-final-second-leg-report-260417 |title=Chelsea 5\u20131 Man City |first=Nicholas |last=Veevers |publisher=The Football Association |date=26 April 2017 |accessdate=10 October 2018}}</ref>\n*[[UEFA Youth League]]: [[2015\u201316 UEFA Youth League|2015\u201316]]<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.uefa.com/uefayouthleague/season=2016/matches/round=2000699/match=2019575/lineups/index.html |title=Paris 1\u20132 Chelsea: Line-ups |publisher=UEFA |accessdate=10 October 2018}}</ref>\n\n'''England U19'''\n*[[UEFA European Under-19 Championship]]: [[2017 UEFA European Under-19 Championship|2017]]<ref name=U19/>\n\n'''Individual'''\n*UEFA European Under-19 Championship Team of the Tournament: [[2017 UEFA European Under-19 Championship#Team of the Tournament|2017]]<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.uefa.com/under19/season=2017/technical-report/uefa-technical-team/index.html |title=The UEFA technical team: Team of the Tournament |publisher=UEFA |accessdate=10 October 2018}}</ref>\n*[[UEFA European Under-19 Championship#Golden Player Award|UEFA European Under-19 Championship Golden Player]]: 2017<ref name=GoldenPlayer/>\n*[[Eredivisie]] Talent of the Month: [[2017\u201318 Eredivisie#Monthly awards|January 2018]]<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.foxsports.nl/nieuws/artikel/2093976/talent-van-maand-mason-mounth |title=Talent van de Maand: Mason Mount |trans-title=Talent of the Month: Mason Mount |publisher=Fox Sports |date=31 January 2018 |accessdate=10 October 2018 |language=Dutch}}</ref>\n*[[SBV Vitesse|Vitesse]] Player of the Year: [[2017\u201318 SBV Vitesse season|2017\u201318]]<ref name=VitessePOTY/>\n*Eredivisie Team of the Year: [[2017\u201318 Eredivisie|2017\u201318]]<ref>{{cite tweet |author=Eredivisie |user=eredivisie |number=994200428136058880 |date=9 May 2018 |title=\u26bd<nowiki>|</nowiki> Het elftal van het seizoen is bekend en dit zijn de 11 namen \ud83d\ude0f\ud83d\udc47\ud83c\udffb Staat je favoriete speler niet in de basis? kijk dan eens bij de wisselspelers \ud83d\udc4b\ud83c\udffb\u27a1 Wie was voor jou de smaakmaker dit seizoen? #eredivisie #onsvoetbal |trans-title=\u26bd<nowiki>|</nowiki> The team of the season is known and these are the 11 names \ud83d\ude0f\ud83d\udc47\ud83c\udffb Is your favourite player not in the base? take a look at the substitutes \ud83d\udc4b\ud83c\udffb\u27a1 Who was the season for you this season? #eredivisie #ourfootball |language=Dutch |accessdate=25 August 2019}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n{{commons category}}\n*[https://www.chelseafc.com/en/teams/first-team/mason-mount?pageTab=biography Profile] at the Chelsea F.C. website\n*[http://www.thefa.com/england/mens-seniors/squad/mason-mount Profile] at the Football Association website\n\n{{Chelsea F.C. squad}}\n{{UEFA European Under-19 Championship awards}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Mount, Mason}}\n[[Category:1999 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Sportspeople from Portsmouth]]\n[[Category:English footballers]]\n[[Category:Association football midfielders]]\n[[Category:Chelsea F.C. players]]\n[[Category:SBV Vitesse players]]\n[[Category:Derby County F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Eredivisie players]]\n[[Category:English Football League players]]\n[[Category:Premier League players]]\n[[Category:England youth international footballers]]\n[[Category:England under-21 international footballers]]\n[[Category:England international footballers]]\n[[Category:English expatriate footballers]]\n[[Category:English expatriate sportspeople in the Netherlands]]\n[[Category:Expatriate footballers in the Netherlands]]\n", "text_old": "{{EngvarB|date=July 2019}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=July 2019}}\n{{Infobox football biography\n| name = Mason Mount\n| image = Chelsea_2_Sheffield_Utd_2_(48655608157)_(cropped).jpg\n| image_size = 200\n| caption = Mount playing for [[Chelsea F.C.|Chelsea]] in 2019\n| fullname = Mason Tony Mount<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.thefa.com/-/media/files/thefaportal/governance-docs/registrations/april-2017.ashx |title=List of players under written contract registered between 01/04/2017 and 30/04/2017 |publisher=The Football Association |format=PDF |page=2 |accessdate=10 February 2018}}</ref>\n| birth_date = {{birth date and age|1999|1|10|df=y}}<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.dcfc.co.uk/teams/player/mason-mount |title=Mason Mount |publisher=Derby County F.C. |accessdate=10 October 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190331065554/https://www.dcfc.co.uk/teams/player/mason-mount |archive-date=31 March 2019 |url-status=dead }}</ref>\n| birth_place = [[Portsmouth]], England\n| height = {{convert|1.78|m|order=flip}}<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.11v11.com/players/mason-mount-253789/ |title=Mason Mount |website=11v11.com |publisher=AFS Enterprises |accessdate=10 October 2018}}</ref>\n| position = [[Midfielder]]\n| currentclub = [[Chelsea F.C.|Chelsea]]\n| clubnumber = 19\n| youthyears1 = 2005\u20132017\n| youthclubs1 = [[Chelsea F.C. Under-23s and Academy|Chelsea]]\n| years1 = 2017\u2013\n| clubs1 = [[Chelsea F.C.|Chelsea]]\n| caps1 = 29\n| goals1 = 6\n| years2 = 2017\u20132018\n| clubs2 = \u2192 [[SBV Vitesse|Vitesse]] (loan)\n| caps2 = 29\n| goals2 = 9\n| years3 = 2018\u20132019\n| clubs3 = \u2192 [[Derby County F.C.|Derby County]] (loan)\n| caps3 = 35\n| goals3 = 8\n| nationalyears1 = 2014\u20132015\n| nationalteam1 = [[England national under-16 football team|England U16]]{{citation needed|date=July 2019}}\n| nationalcaps1 = 5\n| nationalgoals1 = 0\n| nationalyears2 = 2015\u20132016\n| nationalteam2 = [[England national under-17 football team|England U17]]{{citation needed|date=July 2019}}\n| nationalcaps2 = 9\n| nationalgoals2 = 2\n| nationalyears3 = 2016\n| nationalteam3 = [[England national under-18 football team|England U18]]{{citation needed|date=July 2019}}\n| nationalcaps3 = 5\n| nationalgoals3 = 3\n| nationalyears4 = 2017\u20132018\n| nationalteam4 = [[England national under-19 football team|England U19]]<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.englandfootballonline.com/MatchRsl/MatchRslTmU19pg2.html |title=England's matches: The under 19's: 2010\u201320 |website=England Football Online |date=9 April 2019 |accessdate=20 July 2019}}</ref>\n| nationalcaps4 = 16\n| nationalgoals4 = 7\n| nationalyears5 = 2018\u2013\n| nationalteam5 = [[England national under-21 football team|England U21]]<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.englandfootballonline.com/MatchRsl/MatchRslTmU21pg4.html |title=England's matches: The under 21's: 2010\u201320 |website=England Football Online |date=9 September 2019 |accessdate=6 October 2019}}</ref>\n| nationalcaps5 = 4\n| nationalgoals5 = 1\n| nationalyears6 = 2019\u2013\n| nationalteam6 = [[England national football team|England]]\n| nationalcaps6 = 6\n| nationalgoals6 = 1\n| club-update = 16:03, 8 March 2020 (UTC)\n| nationalteam-update = 20:07, 17 November 2019 (UTC)\n}}\n'''Mason Tony Mount''' (born 10 January 1999) is an English professional [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[midfielder]] for {{English football updater|Chelsea}} club [[Chelsea F.C.|Chelsea]] and the [[England national football team|England national team]]. \n\nHe joined Chelsea at the age of six, and began his senior career on loan to [[SBV Vitesse|Vitesse]] in the Dutch [[Eredivisie]] and [[Derby County]] in the [[EFL Championship|Championship]] before making his Chelsea debut in 2019.\n\n==Club career==\n===Chelsea===\n====Youth levels====\n[[File:Mount in 2016.png|thumb|upright|Mount playing for [[Chelsea F.C. Under-23s and Academy|Chelsea U18]] in 2016]]\n\nMount was born in [[Portsmouth]], Hampshire.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.portsmouth.co.uk/sport/football/portsmouth-born-talent-signs-for-chelsea-1-7161622 |title=Portsmouth-born talent signs for Chelsea |first=Jeff |last=Marshman |newspaper=The News |location=Portsmouth |date=15 January 2016 |accessdate=10 October 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180428190724/https://www.portsmouth.co.uk/sport/football/portsmouth-born-talent-signs-for-chelsea-1-7161622 |archive-date=28 April 2018 |url-status=dead }}</ref> His father Tony was a player and manager at [[Non-league football|non-league level]] with local clubs such as [[Havant Town F.C.|Havant Town]].<ref name=wait>[https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/52054333 Mason Mount: How midfielder ended Chelsea's long wait for homegrown star], BBC Sport, 8 April 2020</ref> He was playing under-6 football in local leagues as a four-year-old and spent one day a week training in the academies of [[Portsmouth F.C.|Portsmouth]], [[Southampton F.C.|Southampton]] and [[Chelsea F.C.|Chelsea]].<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.vi.nl/pro/overig/mason-mount-vitesse-pareltje-dat-uitzondering-op-chelsea-regel-moet-worden |title=Mason Mount, Vitesse-pareltje dat uitzondering op Chelsea-regel moet worden |trans-title=Mason Mount, Vitesse gem that should be the exception to Chelsea rule |first=Stef |last=De Bont |website=Voetbal International |date=14 December 2017 |accessdate=10 October 2018 |language=Dutch}}</ref> Mount joined Chelsea at the age of six, in 2005.<ref name=wait/><ref>{{cite news |last1=Fordham |first1=Josh |title=Chelsea starlet Mason Mount signs new five-year contract after impressing on loan with Frank Lampard at Derby County |url=https://talksport.com/football/573242/mason-mount-contract-chelsea-derby/ |accessdate=22 August 2019 |publisher=Talksport |date=15 July 2019|quote=Mount added: \"I joined this club at six-years-old and it was always my goal to play for the first-team one day.}}</ref> He made his [[Chelsea F.C. Under-23s and Academy|under-18]] debut as an under-15 during the [[2013\u201314 Chelsea F.C. season|2013\u201314 season]] and added several more appearances in the [[2014\u201315 Chelsea F.C. season|following season]].{{citation needed|date=October 2018}} Mount went on to play for both under-18 and under-21 teams during the [[2016\u201317 Chelsea F.C. season|2016\u201317 season]], in which he scored 10 goals in 30 appearances.{{citation needed|date=October 2018}} He signed a new four-year contract with Chelsea in July 2017.<ref name=Contract>{{cite web |url=http://www.chelseafc.com/news/latest-news/2017/07/mount-signs-new-deal-and-heads-to-vitesse.html |title=Mount signs new deal and heads to Vitesse |publisher=Chelsea F.C. |date=24 July 2017 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20171007232919/http://www.chelseafc.com/news/latest-news/2017/07/mount-signs-new-deal-and-heads-to-vitesse.html |archivedate=7 October 2017}}</ref>\n\n====Loans to Vitesse and Derby County====\nMount joined Dutch [[Eredivisie]] club [[SBV Vitesse|Vitesse]] on 24 July 2017 on a season-long [[Loan (sports)|loan]].<ref name=Contract/> He made his first-team debut on 26 August, as a 77th-minute [[Substitute (association football)|substitute]] during Vitesse's 2\u20131 home defeat against [[AZ Alkmaar|AZ]].<ref name=Soccerway/><ref>{{cite web |url=https://uk.soccerway.com/matches/2017/08/26/netherlands/eredivisie/sbv-vitesse/stichting-az/2462357/ |title=Vitesse vs. AZ 1\u20132 |website=Soccerway |publisher=Perform Group |accessdate=10 October 2018}}</ref> The following month, he was given his first start in Vitesse's [[KNVB Cup]] first-round defeat away to fifth-tier team [[AVV Swift|Swift]], playing the full 90 minutes of the 0\u20130 draw, which Swift won in a [[Penalty shoot-out (association football)|penalty shoot-out]].<ref name=Soccerway/><ref>{{cite web |url=https://uk.soccerway.com/matches/2017/09/20/netherlands/knvb-beker/swift/sbv-vitesse/2580810/ |title=Swift vs. Vitesse 0\u20130 |website=Soccerway |publisher=Perform Group |accessdate=10 October 2018}}</ref> He scored his first goal for Vitesse on 1 October in the 76th minute of a 1\u20131 home draw with [[FC Utrecht|Utrecht]].<ref name=Soccerway/><ref>{{cite web |url=https://uk.soccerway.com/matches/2017/10/01/netherlands/eredivisie/sbv-vitesse/stichting-fc-utrecht/2462399/ |title=Vitesse vs. Utrecht 1\u20131 |website=Soccerway |publisher=Perform Group |accessdate=10 October 2018}}</ref> Mount went onto appear in the Eredivisie Team of the Week on several occasions and win the Vitesse Player of the Year award.<ref name=VitessePOTY>{{cite web |url=https://weaintgotnohistory.sbnation.com/2018/4/29/17299438/mason-mount-becomes-third-chelsea-loanee-to-win-vitesse-player-of-the-year-award |title=Mason Mount becomes third Chelsea loanee to win Vitesse Player of the Year award |first=Ram |last=Srinivas |website=We Ain't Got No History |publisher=Vox Media |date=29 April 2018 |accessdate=10 October 2018}}</ref>\n\nDuring Vitesse's Eredivisie European play-off semi-final first leg against [[ADO Den Haag]] on 9 May 2018, Mount scored his first hat-trick, as Vitesse won 5\u20132 away.<ref name=Soccerway/> In the second leg, Mount scored in a 2\u20131 win as Vitesse won 7\u20133 on aggregate.<ref name=Soccerway/> In the first leg of the final against Utrecht, Mount opened the scoring but was booked and therefore suspended for the second leg.<ref name=Soccerway/> Mount made 39 appearances in all competitions for Vitesse, scoring 14 times, before returning to Chelsea.\n\nMount joined [[EFL Championship|Championship]] club [[Derby County F.C.|Derby County]] on 17 July 2018 on a season-long loan.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/44860172 |title=Derby County sign youngsters Mason Mount and Harry Wilson on loan |website=BBC Sport |date=17 July 2018 |accessdate=17 July 2018}}</ref> He scored a 60th-minute equaliser on his debut for Derby on 3 August 2018, during a 2\u20131 away victory over [[Reading F.C.|Reading]].<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/44976502 |title=Reading 1\u20132 Derby County |first=Adam |last=Williams |website=BBC Sport |date=3 August 2018 |accessdate=10 October 2018}}</ref>\n\nMount was sidelined for two months after suffering a [[hamstring injury]] in a [[FA Cup]] game against [[Accrington Stanley F.C.|Accrington Stanley]].<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.portsmouth.co.uk/news/fa-cup-mason-mount-injured-as-derby-edge-accrington-wolves-deny-shrewsbury-doncaster-join-portsmouth-and-qpr-in-hat-1-8785996 |title=FA Cup: Mason Mount injured as Derby edge Accrington\u2026 Wolves deny Shrewsbury\u2026  Doncaster join Portsmouth and QPR in hat |newspaper=The News |date=26 January 2019 |accessdate=2 April 2019}}</ref> He returned in a 6\u20131 win over [[Rotherham United F.C.|Rotherham United]], winning a penalty for teammate [[Martyn Waghorn]] and later scoring.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/47676104 |title=Derby County 6\u20131 Rotherham United |website=BBC Sport |date=30 March 2019 |accessdate=2 April 2019}}</ref> Two weeks later, he scored his first senior [[hat-trick]] in a 4\u20130 [[EFL Championship|Championship]] league game against [[Bolton Wanderers F.C.|Bolton Wanderers]],<ref>{{cite web |url=https://tribuna.com/en/chelsea/news/3351509/ |title=Mount scores first senior hat-trick sending Derby closer to premier league promotion |publisher=Fedor Gavrilov |date=13 April 2019 |accessdate=16 April 2019}}</ref> keeping Derby in contention for the promotion [[EFL Championship play-offs|playoff]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.derbytelegraph.co.uk/sport/football/football-news/gallery/best-pictures-mason-mount-hat-2756168 |title=The best pictures as Mason Mount hat-trick keeps Derby County play-off hopes alive |publisher=Jonny Bonell |date=13 April 2019 |accessdate=16 April 2019}}</ref>\n\n====First-team breakthrough====\nOn 15 July 2019, Mount signed a new five-year deal with Chelsea.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.chelseafc.com/en/news/2019/07/15/mason-mount-commits-to-chelsea-with-new-contract-signed |title=MASON MOUNT COMMITS TO CHELSEA WITH NEW CONTRACT SIGNED |publisher=Chelsea F.C. |date=15 July 2019 |accessdate=16 July 2019}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/48993844 |title=Mason Mount: Chelsea midfielder signs five-year contract |date=15 July 2019 |website=BBC Sport}}</ref> He made his competitive debut for Chelsea on 11 August 2019 in a 0\u20134 away defeat to [[Manchester United F.C.|Manchester United]] in the [[Premier League]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.chelseafc.com/en/news/2019/08/11/report--manchester-united-v-chelsea |title=REPORT: MAN UNITED 4 CHELSEA 0 |publisher=Chelsea F.C. |date=11 August 2019 |accessdate=11 August 2019}}</ref> He scored his first Chelsea goal a week later against [[Leicester City F.C.|Leicester City]] during [[Frank Lampard]]'s home debut as manager at [[Stamford Bridge (stadium)|Stamford Bridge]], a 1\u20131 draw,<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.goal.com/en/match/chelsea-v-leicester-city/6ksyqoht9ras6zwyvks09fofe|title=Chelsea 1-1 Leicester City: Mount hits the heights before Foxes bite back|date=18 August 2019|website=Goal}}</ref> and added another in the next game away to [[Norwich City F.C.|Norwich City]].<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.chelseafc.com/en/news/2019/08/24/match-report--norwich-city-vs-chelsea|title=MATCH REPORT: NORWICH CITY 2 CHELSEA 3 |date=24 August 2019|website=Goal}}</ref> On 17 September, he suffered an ankle injury against [[Valencia CF|Valencia]] in the [[2019\u201320 UEFA Champions League|Champions League]] opener.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/49736574|title=Mason Mount injury: Chelsea to assess ankle over next 48 hours|date=17 September 2019|publisher=BBC Sport}}</ref>\n\nIn March 2020, Mount was spoken to by Chelsea for ignoring [[Self-isolating|self-isolation]] rules during the [[2020 coronavirus pandemic in the United Kingdom|coronavirus pandemic]]. While the entire squad was made to self-isolate due to the infection of [[Callum Hudson-Odoi]], Mount had gone to play football with friends including West Ham's [[Declan Rice]].<ref>{{cite news |last1=Hytner |first1=David |title=Chelsea act after Mason Mount ignores coronavirus self-isolation advice |url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/2020/mar/16/mason-mount-warned-by-chelsea-after-breaking-coronavirus-self-isolation |accessdate=5 April 2020 |work=The Guardian |date=16 March 2020}}</ref>\n\n==International career==\n===Youth===\nMount has represented England at [[England national under-16 football team|under-16]], [[England national under-17 football team|under-17]], [[England national under-18 football team|under-18]] and [[England national under-19 football team|under-19]] levels.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.thefa.com/england/all-teams/players?p=356955 |title=Mason Mount |publisher=The Football Association |accessdate=12 August 2017}}{{dead link|date=October 2018}}</ref> Mount represented the under-17s at the [[2016 UEFA European Under-17 Championship]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.thefa.com/news/2016/may/04/euro-finals-squad-announced-040516 |title=England under-17s squad named for Euro Championship |first=Nicholas |last=Veevers |publisher=The Football Association |date=4 May 2016 |accessdate=10 October 2018}}</ref>\n\nMount was included in the under-19 team for the [[2017 UEFA European Under-19 Championship]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.thefa.com/news/2017/jun/26/england-u19-squad-for-euros-260617 |title=Squad for U19 Euro |publisher=The Football Association |date=26 June 2017 |accessdate=10 October 2018}}</ref> He provided the assist for [[Lukas Nmecha]] to score the winning goal against [[Portugal national under-19 football team|Portugal]] in the final.<ref name=U19>{{cite web |url=http://www.thefa.com/news/2017/jul/15/report-2017-uefa-u19-championship-final-portugal-england-150717 |title=Portugal 1\u20132 England U19s |first=Andy |last=Walker |publisher=The Football Association |date=15 July 2017 |accessdate=10 October 2018}}</ref> He was subsequently named [[UEFA European Under-19 Championship#Golden Player Award|Golden Player]] of the tournament.<ref name=GoldenPlayer>{{cite web |url=https://www.uefa.com/under19/history/season=2017/goldenplayer/index.html |title=2017: Mason Mount |publisher=UEFA |date=25 July 2017 |accessdate=10 October 2018}}</ref>\n\nOn 27 May 2019, Mount was included in England's 23-man squad for the [[2019 UEFA European Under-21 Championship]].<ref>{{Cite news |title=ENGLAND U21S SQUAD NAMED BY AIDY BOOTHROYD FOR THIS SUMMER'S EURO FINALS IN ITALY |url=http://www.thefa.com/news/2019/may/26/england-u21s-squad-named-for-euros-270519 |publisher=The Football Association |date=27 May 2019 |accessdate=19 June 2019}}</ref>\n\n===Senior===\nFollowing his impressive season with Vitesse, Mount was invited by manager [[Gareth Southgate]] to train with the [[England national football team|senior team]] for a week ahead of the [[2018 FIFA World Cup]].<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.portsmouth.co.uk/sport/football/pompey/portsmouth-born-mount-to-train-with-southgate-s-england-squad-1-8503986 |title=Portsmouth-born Mount to train with Southgate's England squad |first=Will |last=Rooney |newspaper=The News |location=Portsmouth |date=18 May 2018 |accessdate=10 October 2018}}</ref> He was called up to the senior team for the [[UEFA Nations League]] matches against [[Croatia national football team|Croatia]] and [[Spain national football team|Spain]] in October 2018.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/45744731 |title=James Maddison, Jadon Sancho and Mason Mount named in England squad |website=BBC Sport |date=4 October 2018 |accessdate=10 October 2018}}</ref>\n\nMount made his debut for the England senior team on 7 September 2019 as a 67th-minute substitute in England's 4\u20130 home win over [[Bulgaria national football team|Bulgaria]] in [[UEFA Euro 2020 qualifying]].<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/49533275 |title=England 4\u20130 Bulgaria |first=Phil |last=McNulty |website=BBC Sport |date=7 September 2019 |accessdate=7 September 2019}}</ref> He scored his first goal for England on 17 November in a 4\u20130 away win against [[Kosovo national football team|Kosovo]] in UEFA Euro 2020 qualifying.<ref name=Kosovo>{{cite news |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/50160458 |title=Kosovo 0\u20134 England |first=Phil |last=McNulty |website=BBC Sport |date=17 November 2019 |accessdate=17 November 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Career statistics==\n===Club===\n{{updated|match played 8 March 2020}}\n\n{| class=wikitable style=text-align:center\n|+ Appearances and goals by club, season and competition\n|-\n!rowspan=2|Club\n!rowspan=2|Season\n!colspan=3|League\n!colspan=2|National Cup{{efn|Includes [[KNVB Cup]], [[FA Cup]]}}\n!colspan=2|League Cup{{efn|Includes [[EFL Cup]]}}\n!colspan=2|Europe\n!colspan=2|Other\n!colspan=2|Total\n|-\n!Division!!Apps!!Goals!!Apps!!Goals!!Apps!!Goals!!Apps!!Goals!!Apps!!Goals!!Apps!!Goals\n|-\n|[[Chelsea F.C. Under-23s and Academy|Chelsea U23]]\n|[[2016\u201317 EFL Trophy|2016\u201317]]<ref name=sb1617>{{soccerbase season|96788|2016|accessdate=10 October 2018}}</ref>\n|colspan=3|\u2014||colspan=2|\u2014||colspan=2|\u2014||colspan=2|\u2014||3{{efn|Appearances in [[EFL Trophy]]}}||0||3||0\n|-\n|[[SBV Vitesse|Vitesse]] (loan)\n|[[2017\u