{"title_page": "Deniliquin Football Club", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=January 2018}}\n{{Use Australian English|date=January 2018}}\n\n{{Infobox Australian football club\n| clubname        = Deniliquin\n| image           = Deniliquin fnc logo.png\n| image_size      = 150px\n| color1 = #0D4695\n| color2 = #ffcc00\n| color3 = solid #ffcc00\n| fullname        = Deniliquin Football Netball Club\n| formernames     = \n| nicknames       = ''Rams''\n| formernicknames = \n| motto           = \n| clubsong        =  \n| season          = \n| afterfinals     = \n| home&away       = \n| pre-season      = \n| topgoalkicker   = \n| bestandfairest  = \n| founded         = {{Start date and age|1933}}\n| dissolved       = \n| colours         = {{colorbox|#0D4695}} {{colorbox|#ffcc00}}\n| league          = [[Murray Football League|Murray FNL]]\n| owners          = \n| president       =  \n| chairman        = \n| ceo             = \n| coach           =  \n| captain         = \n| ground          =  \n| capacity        = \n| premierships    =  \n| kit_alt1        = \n| pattern_b1      = _amber_stripes \n| pattern_sh1     = _goldsides\n| pattern_so1     =  _goldtop\n| body1           = 0D4695\n| shorts1         = 0D4695\n| socks1          = 0D4695\n| kit_alt2        = \n| pattern_b2      = \n| pattern_sh2     = \n| pattern_so2     = \n| body2           = \n| shorts2         = \n| socks2          = \n| url             = \n| jumper          = \n| current         = \n}}\n\nThe '''Deniliquin Football Club''', nicknamed the '''''Rams''''', is an [[Australian rules football]] and [[netball]] club based in the town of [[Deniliquin, New South Wales|Deniliquin]] located in the [[Riverina]] district of [[New South Wales, Australia|New South Wales]].\n\nThe club teams currently compete in the [[Murray Football League|Murray FNL]], which the Deniliquin football squad joined in 1949.\n\nFootball appears to have been played in and around Deniliquin as early as the 1870s, but today's Deniliquin FC was born some six decades later, in 1933. \n\nSeveral Deniliquin players have gone on to play in the [[Australian Football League|Victorian and Australian Football Leagues]] (VFL and AFL), including [[Leo Barry]] and [[Peter McIntyre (Australian footballer)|Peter McIntyre]]. Additionally, former VFL footballers including [[Graham Ion]], [[Kevin O'Donnell (footballer)|Kevin O'Donnell]] and [[Peter O'Donohue]] have coached Deniliquin.\n\n==Premierships==\n* [[Murray Football League]] (14):\n** 1957, 1966, 1972, 1973, 1975, 1976, 1985, 1986, 1996, 2001, 2002, 2003, 2004, 2011\n* Echuca Football League (3):\n** 1933, 1934, 1935\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* [http://websites.sportstg.com/club_info.cgi?client=1-6183-80773-0-0 SportsTG site]\n* [https://www.facebook.com/Deniliquin-Rams-Football-Netball-Club-630098554000367/ Facebook page]\n* [http://www.footypedia.com/00001707.htm Footypedia page]\n\n{{Commons category|position=left}}\n{{Murray football league}}\n\n[[Category:Murray Football League clubs]]\n[[Category:Deniliquin]]\n[[Category:1933 establishments in Australia]]\n[[Category:Australian rules football clubs in New South Wales]]\n[[Category:Sports clubs established in 1933]]\n[[Category:Australian netball teams]]\n\n{{AFL-team-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Use dmy dates|date=January 2018}}\n{{Use Australian English|date=January 2018}}\n\n{{Infobox Australian football club\n| clubname        = Deniliquin\n| image           = Deniliquin fnc logo.png\n| image_size      = 150px\n| color1 = #0D4695\n| color2 = #ffcc00\n| color3 = solid #ffcc00\n| fullname        = Deniliquin Football Netball Club\n| formernames     = \n| nicknames       = ''Rams''\n| formernicknames = \n| motto           = \n| clubsong        =  \n| season          = \n| afterfinals     = \n| home&away       = \n| pre-season      = \n| topgoalkicker   = \n| bestandfairest  = \n| founded         = {{Start date and age|1933}}\n| dissolved       = \n| colours         = {{colorbo